## Document Output Format

All documents produced by agents MUST be saved as **styled HTML files** — NOT markdown (.md).

### Rules for ALL document agents:

- **Output format:** `.html` files with embedded CSS styling
- **Save location:** `docs/` folder in the project root
- **Styling:** Professional, clean design — modern sans-serif font (Inter, system-ui)
- **Structure:** Self-contained, single-file document (CSS in `<style>`)
- **Naming:** kebab-case, e.g. `docs/brd.html`, `docs/srs.html`

### Rules for Prototype / Wireframe output (@uxui):

- **Save location:** `docs/prototype/` folder
- **Use Tailwind CDN** for rapid styling
- **Each screen = one HTML file**
- **Index file:** `docs/prototype/index.html` with links to all screens
- **Component Library:** `docs/prototype/components.html` — showcases ALL UI components (buttons, inputs, tables, cards, navigation, etc.) with all states
- **Use design tokens** from Q22–Q26 answers below — no hardcoded colors/fonts/spacing

### Document Portal — MANDATORY

All documents viewed through `docs/index.html`.
Every agent that creates a doc MUST register it in `docs/index.html`.

