## Project Workflow — The 6-Gate Approval System

```
GATE 0 — Project Setup → auto (GitHub repo + Notion board)
GATE 1 — Discovery     → STOP → wait for: "Approved" (BRD + SRS)
GATE 2 — Architecture  → STOP → wait for: "Approved" (all 9 docs)
GATE 3 — Task Setup    → STOP → wait for: "Task list approved" → create GitHub Issues + Notion tasks
GATE 4 — Per Task      → STOP → wait for: "go" (per task) + PR review + approval
GATE 5 — Quality       → STOP → wait for: "Approved" → merge to main, tag release
```

### GATE 0 — Project Setup (automatic)

- DevOps → create GitHub repo + branch strategy
- PM → create Notion task board
- DevOps → save .project.env

### GATE 1 — Discovery

- @ba asks Q1–Q31, writes CLAUDE.md
- @ba writes BRD → `docs/brd.html`
- @ba + @techlead write SRS → `docs/srs.html`
- STOP and wait for "Approved"

### GATE 2 — Architecture & Design (all 9 docs)

- @dba → `docs/database-design.html`
- @backend → `docs/api-reference.html`
- @security → `docs/security-design.html`
- @devops → `docs/infrastructure-guide.html`
- @qa → `docs/test-strategy.html`
- @uxui → `docs/prototype/index.html` + `docs/prototype/components.html`
- @pm → `docs/project-plan.html`
- PAIR REVIEW: cross-check all outputs for conflicts → resolve before showing gate
- **COMPLETION CHECK:** All 9 docs + component library must exist before "Approved"

### GATE 3 — Task Breakdown + Setup

- @pm breaks scope into: Epic → Feature → Task
- STOP and wait for "Task list approved"
- Then: create GitHub Issues + Notion tasks (automated)
- STOP and wait for "Confirmed. Start the project."

### GATE 4 — Per-Task Development

- State task name + GitHub issue number
- Show branch name → wait for "go"
- Build with tests → PR REVIEW (architecture, code quality, security, performance, testing, docs)
- STOP → wait for "Approved" or "Merge"

### GATE 5 — Quality & Delivery

- QA → run all tests, coverage report
- Security → OWASP checklist
- DevOps → CI/CD pipeline passing
- Docs → README, API docs, deployment guide
- PM → verify all Notion tasks → Done
- STOP → wait for "Approved" → merge to main, tag release

