## Notion ↔ GitHub Sync Rules

| Event       | Notion Status | GitHub                         |
| ----------- | ------------- | ------------------------------ |
| Task starts | In Progress   | Issue assigned, branch created |
| PR opened   | In Review     | PR linked to issue             |
| PR merged   | Done          | Issue closed, branch deleted   |

---

## Approval Keywords

| You say                         | What happens                              |
| ------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| `continue` / resume             | Check progress.json → resume              |
| `Approved`                      | Documents → task breakdown                |
| `Task list approved`            | Create in Notion + GitHub                 |
| `Confirmed. Start the project.` | Begin Gate 4, first task                  |
| `go`                            | Agent starts coding                       |
| `next task`                     | Next task + branch, waits for go          |
| `pause`                         | Stop after current task                   |
| `stop`                          | Stop immediately                          |

